He played 22 matches for the club in his first season in Major League Soccer, scoring two goals and providing one assist -- a performance he said he is proud of, as Covid-19 pandemic had affected him. 

“The first season was a little bit difficult because of Covid-19, but when we were back to playing, it was good and the team performed well, so I am happy with my first season. 

“Because in every season you need to aim higher. Hopefully everyone can come back fit and we can take it from there and do better than last season,” said Wanyama. 



